GitoriousLdap
=============
To install it (from your Gitorious root):
bundle exec ./script/plugin install git://github.com/gapcoder/gitorious-ldap-plugin.git

This plugins integrates LDAP authentification server with your Gitorious models.
It can (whe it will be realised):
 - scan users from the ldap
 - scan groups from the ldap
 - attach users to the groups
 - attach existing projects with ldap access settings to the Gitorious

All plugin work is in rake tasks under space 'ldap'
bundle exec rake -T | grep ldap - will show you available tasks

Example
=======
In your gitorious root :

bundle exec rake ldap:sync_users



